SSH Server: Password Authentication configure SSH server to manage a server from remote computer, SSH client.

Step 1: Install openssh-server
  sudo apt-get install openssh-server
  
Step 2: Enable SSH
  sudo systemctl enable ssh
  
Step 3: Start SSH
  sudo systemctl start ssh
  
Step 4: Configuring a firewall
  sudo ufw allow ssh
  sudo ufw enable
  sudo ufw status

Step 5: Test your connection
  ssh username@ip
